  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-4892">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 1. </span>
      Do the following:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-4892 mb-requirement-id-4893">
        (a) Describe the safety precautions you should take when handling and
        caring for a horse. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/B5KeqtLZoUA?si=FD2BQR4jCnU4E6OS"
          target="_blank"
          >Safety Precautions When Handling Horses (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-4892 mb-requirement-id-4894">
        (b) Describe the fire safety precautions you should take in a barn and
        around horses. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/w-05f23oJVA" target="_blank"
          >Barn Fire Safety (video)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-4910">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 2. </span>
      Name 15 parts of a horse and discuss the function of each with your
      counselor. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
      <a href="https://youtu.be/y369q1jh8HQ" target="_blank"
        >Parts of a Horse (video)</a
      ><br />
      <a
        href="https://filestore.scouting.org/filestore/Merit_Badge_ReqandRes/Requirement%20Resources/Horsemanship/Parts%20of%20a%20Horse.jpg"
        target="_blank"
        >Parts of a Horse (filled) (PDF)</a
      ><br />
      <a
        href="https://filestore.scouting.org/filestore/Merit_Badge_ReqandRes/Requirement%20Resources/Horsemanship/Parts%20of%20a%20Horse%20-%20blank%20worksheet.pdf"
        target="_blank"
        >Parts of a Horse (blank) (PDF)</a
      >
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-4911">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 3. </span>
      Name four breeds of horses. Explain the special features for which each
      breed is known. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
      <a href="https://youtu.be/FiBBNX8WszQ" target="_blank"
        >Ten Popular Horse Breeds (video)</a
      ><br />
      <a href="https://youtu.be/jwZj65SHdcw?si=hK8GTTDsRlUT5kAZ" target="_blank"
        >Six Popular Horse Breeds (video)</a
      >
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-4912">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 4. </span>
      Describe the symptoms of colic. Name and describe four other horse health
      problems. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
      <a href="https://youtu.be/_ZeUDXMmSXE?si=mw4HfkBBedTRvh5a" target="_blank"
        >Health Problems in Horses (video)</a
      >
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-4913">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 5. </span>
      Explain what conformation is and why it is important. Explain the
      difference between lameness and unsoundness. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
      <a href="https://www.youtube.com/shorts/Ica4d4jK2eo" target="_blank"
        >Lameness vs. Unsoundness (video)</a
      ><br />
      <a href="https://youtu.be/c9Mn9RP39lE?si=T2D88HPDsxFjWU8v" target="_blank"
        >Signs of Lameness (video)</a
      >
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-4914">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 6. </span>
      Explain the importance of hoof care and why a horse might need to wear
      shoes. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
      <a href="https://youtu.be/whbZsicSv-k" target="_blank"
        >How to Clean Horse Hooves (video)</a
      >
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-4915">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 7. </span>
      Demonstrate how to groom a horse, including picking hooves and caring for
      a horse after a ride. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
      <a href="https://youtu.be/fdGhd2phEHs" target="_blank"
        >Caring for a Horse (video)</a
      ><br />
      <a href="https://youtu.be/9Leym8QeBM8" target="_blank"
        >How to Groom a Horse (video)</a
      >
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-4916">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 8. </span>
      Explain how to determine what and how much to feed a horse and why the
      amount and kind of feed are changed according to the activity level and
      the breed of horse. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
      <a href="https://youtu.be/AcgfzGhaoes" target="_blank"
        >What Do Horses Eat? (video)</a
      >
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-4895">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 9. </span>
      Do the following:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-4895 mb-requirement-id-4896">
        (a) Name 10 parts of the saddle and bridle that you will use, and
        explain how to care for this equipment. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=CXkV6LxGJF8" target="_blank"
          >Parts of a Saddle (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-4895 mb-requirement-id-4897">
        (b) Show how to properly saddle and bridle a horse. <br /><i
          >Resources:</i
        >
        <a href="https://youtu.be/MZHl9zBHD10" target="_blank"
          >How to Saddle a Horse (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/sI7A5aTFUnE" target="_blank"
          >How to Bridle a Horse (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-4895 mb-requirement-id-4898">
        (c) Demonstrate how to safely mount and dismount a horse. <br /><i
          >Resources:</i
        >
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/a40XR220wd8?si=yAKM4J6yhQAYZufm"
          target="_blank"
          >Using a Mounting Block and Adjusting Tack (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/p3T7tUwyNBg?si=Rnuup5QA8iw_DLlU"
          target="_blank"
          >Mounting and Dismounting a Horse (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/CafSxVC-1I8" target="_blank"
          >How to Mount a Horse (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/NC9Tr2hXfFk?si=-mIGi5Woskl7jBPn"
          target="_blank"
          >How to Ride a Horse (video)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-4909">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 10. </span>
      Explain and demonstrate how to approach and lead a horse safely from a
      stall, corral, or field and how to tie the horse securely. <br /><i
        >Resource:</i
      >
      <a href="https://youtu.be/AsP38UPNHvI" target="_blank"
        >How to Lead a Horse (video)</a
      >
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-4899">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 11. </span>
      On level ground, continuously do the following movements after safely
      mounting the horse. Do them correctly, at ease, and in harmony with the
      horse. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
      <a href="https://youtu.be/uZ_5lxUyCdw" target="_blank"
        >How to Steer Your Horse (video)</a
      ><br />
      <a href="https://youtu.be/fV7kuUrjutY" target="_blank"
        >How to Ride a Horse (video)</a
      ><br />
      <a href="https://youtu.be/oFy6FqQ_PXM?si=Qk7V2jJdKykcp9il" target="_blank"
        >Riding Despite Physical Challenges (video)</a
      >
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-4899 mb-requirement-id-4900">
        (a) Walk the horse in a straight line for 60 feet.
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-4899 mb-requirement-id-4901">
        (b) Walk the horse in a half-circle of not more than 16 feet in radius.
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-4899 mb-requirement-id-4902">
        (c) Trot or jog the horse in a straight line for 60 feet. <br /><i
          >Resource:</i
        >
        <a href="https://youtu.be/-3CMZSbQRgg" target="_blank"
          >How to Trot a Horse (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-4899 mb-requirement-id-4903">
        (d) Trot or jog the horse in a half-circle of not more than 30 feet in
        radius. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/KCSkmYEQxEg?si=ET5yK-3VM_Pjzae3"
          target="_blank"
          >Tips for Trotting (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-4899 mb-requirement-id-4906">
        (e) Halt straight. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/GJ0Y_ZaCSmo" target="_blank"
          >How to Stop Your Horse (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-4899 mb-requirement-id-4907">
        (f) Back up straight four paces. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/aolJGYfOZI0" target="_blank"
          >How to Back Up a Horse (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-4899 mb-requirement-id-4908">
        (g) Halt and dismount. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/vBdXfiNXu7I?si=Cb12AYTlH2J_lbtg"
          target="_blank"
          >Mount and Dismount a Horse (video)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
</div>
